Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.75,0:00:04.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Encounters are mysterious!\NBut cases are even more so!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.08,0:00:06.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so glad I'm with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.29,0:00:09.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today's stage is a clock manor!\NThe case's alarms all ring together!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.21,0:00:11.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sees the\Nsingle truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.44,0:00:13.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and looks like a kid but\Nhas the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.76,0:00:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.00,0:01:56.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Case of the Mysterious\NBandit Mansion (Part 1)."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.85,0:02:07.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Dear Mori Kogoro.\NI'm sorry for the sudden letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.73,0:02:11.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Getting directly to the point,\NI would like you, the great detective,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.77,0:02:16.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to solve the mysteries concerning\Nstrange events in my home.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.15,0:02:22.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's actually an old mansion\Ngiven to me by my grandfather,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.07,0:02:24.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who passed away very recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.16,0:02:29.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since moving in, strange events\Nhave been occurring daily,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.37,0:02:34.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I've even had the feeling\Nthat I'm being watched lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.29,0:02:39.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I tried to figure it out on my own,\Nas I'm a simple mystery writer,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.05,0:02:43.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but seeing as I haven't been here\Nlong and don't know the house well,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.30,0:02:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I figured I wouldn't discover\Nanything on my own,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.52,0:02:49.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which is why I've sent you this letter."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.52,0:03:00.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"On his deathbed, my grandfather\Nsaid the mansion was special,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.07,0:03:03.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which I find very strange now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.07,0:03:07.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're interested,\Nplease come before 10:30 a.m.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.79,0:03:11.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I look forward to hearing\Nfrom you. Nakamura Misao."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.71,0:03:15.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm coming, Misao-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.80,0:03:21.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've deduced that she's a lonely,\Ntalented woman in her late 20s!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.09,0:03:26.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure? It sounded like some\Nglum guy in his early 30s to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.93,0:03:33.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How dumb! Why would I rent a car\Nand go there on a Sunday then?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.81,0:03:38.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't you have told if it was\Na man or a woman on the phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.36,0:03:46.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't call. I'm gonna show\Nup and make an exciting entrance!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.66,0:03:49.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want\Nto excite this person for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.45,0:03:53.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's such a lost cause...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.87,0:03:58.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?\NIs it a man or a woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.25,0:04:01.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know. The handwriting is nice...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.63,0:04:05.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it is a woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.89,0:04:14.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad! That's dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.56,0:04:22.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sorry! I messed up!\NI haven't done this in a while!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.65,0:04:25.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me, Misao-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.82,0:04:27.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one can forgive this!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.21,0:04:37.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'll take the train back.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.38,0:04:42.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you talking about?\NThat was a pleasant family drive!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.42,0:04:44.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You call that pleasant?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.22,0:04:50.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just look at this refreshing\Nsunlight coming through the leaves!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.85,0:04:53.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't it just relieve your mind?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.64,0:04:57.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I'm relieved we\Nactually made it to our destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.19,0:05:09.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whadya think? This large mansion\Nis surrounded by trees and nature!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.20,0:05:14.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... "It's so lonely for a single woman!"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.58,0:05:20.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Misao-{\i1}san{\i0}! At long last,\Nyour Mori Kogoro has arrived!"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.25,0:05:25.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've recently started to\Nunderstand why Mom left you...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.92,0:05:26.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.94,0:05:38.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.27,0:05:45.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}! You came!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.65,0:05:48.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, we can say hello inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.28,0:05:51.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.45,0:05:54.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See! I told you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.58,0:05:58.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, did you send this letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.54,0:06:02.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, the person who wrote that\Nletter is my three-years-younger--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.75,0:06:04.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your younger sister?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.42,0:06:07.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My younger brother, Misao.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.63,0:06:08.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi, there!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.30,0:06:12.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.55,0:06:15.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the one who\Ninherited this mansion,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.10,0:06:18.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it's so big that\NI moved in with my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.19,0:06:21.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to your arm?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.15,0:06:24.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hurt it while moving some shelves.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.61,0:06:27.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's bad. Especially for a writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.45,0:06:33.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's only a sprain. The doctor just\Nwent overboard and wrapped it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.66,0:06:36.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyways, come inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.46,0:06:42.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.25,0:06:44.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't this seem strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.80,0:06:50.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a tiger on that pillar,\Nbut not on this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.76,0:06:53.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It has weird holes instead...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.01,0:06:57.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe they planned to put\Nsomething there, but decided not to?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.14,0:06:58.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.98,0:07:00.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come in already.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.89,0:07:02.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.19,0:07:03.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.56,0:07:04.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.16,0:07:14.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! How cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.16,0:07:18.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What an amazing collection!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.50,0:07:21.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are animals on almost\Nall the furniture and dishes!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.37,0:07:25.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Is this a seal?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.29,0:07:29.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}. That's a walrus.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.51,0:07:31.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.05,0:07:36.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All this junk everywhere\Nmakes the place stuffy...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.68,0:07:41.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Surprised? Our late grandfather\Nabsolutely loved animals!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.14,0:07:46.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He always used to say\Nthat animals that hunted to live
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.61,0:07:53.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,were much better than humans\Nwho fool others out of sheer greed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.95,0:07:59.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Animals aside, there\Nsure are a lot of clocks here...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.04,0:08:03.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But of course.\NOur grandfather was a clockmaker!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.71,0:08:06.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A clockmaker?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.46,0:08:09.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. His name was Izubuchi Monjiro.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.38,0:08:12.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He made quite a name for himself;
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.13,0:08:17.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Monjiro's clocks last a lifetime,"\Npeople came to say!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.89,0:08:21.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then this digital\Nbunny clock was his, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.73,0:08:25.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, our grandfather only\Nmade screw-operated clocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.90,0:08:28.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He probably just\Ncollected those ones for fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.73,0:08:32.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. There's a crack\Non this digital clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.99,0:08:37.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He must've handled things\Nhe didn't make without much care.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.74,0:08:40.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See? This one, too. And this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.29,0:08:44.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange. He always\Ntook great care of his things...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.12,0:08:47.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't this clock seem strange too?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.59,0:08:51.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like something\Nused to be attached to it...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.59,0:08:54.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It probably came off when\Nhe dropped it or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.80,0:08:56.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.60,0:09:02.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this a photo of Monjiro-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.22,0:09:05.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! It's from quite a long time ago, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.31,0:09:08.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's the girl with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.11,0:09:12.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's his friend's granddaughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.23,0:09:17.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He always used to take me\Nand my brother to the golf course.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.70,0:09:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then this golf bag\Nwas Monjiro-{\i1}san'{\i0}s?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.33,0:09:23.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Demon"?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.62,0:09:32.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, it's what they call\Npeople who score over 100 in golf.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.92,0:09:34.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our grandfather could\Nnever improve his score,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.92,0:09:37.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so we gave him that as a joke present.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.30,0:09:42.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, wasn't "Demons"\Nthe name of an old bandit gang?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.22,0:09:48.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, the gang that only\Nstole from bad companies and people!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.85,0:09:54.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be dumb.\NThose were the Goblins, not the Demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.53,0:10:00.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry! I should've been helping!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.70,0:10:05.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here it is again!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.66,0:10:10.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the other cups have animals\Non their handles, but not this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.67,0:10:14.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it's been carefully\Nfiled down afterward.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.42,0:10:19.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the animal had fallen off,\Nit could've been easily glued back on.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.76,0:10:21.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So why?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.30,0:10:22.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.56,0:10:25.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.10,0:10:27.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll clean this up!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.31,0:10:28.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, thanks...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.19,0:10:34.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, could you tell me about these\Nstrange happenings you spoke of?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.53,0:10:37.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you mean the clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.36,0:10:39.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Clock?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.53,0:10:43.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,10:48... Perfect timing...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.87,0:10:46.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to the study.\NI'll let you see for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.25,0:10:54.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn. It's stuck again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.79,0:10:58.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, have you forgotten?\NYou gotta kick the bottom right part.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.05,0:11:02.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.93,0:11:04.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.31,0:11:10.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You leave the curtains shut,\Neven though it's so stifling in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.64,0:11:15.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like I mentioned in the letter.\NIt feels like someone's watching us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.98,0:11:17.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.62,0:11:26.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a hole over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.49,0:11:31.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really? Well, this house\Nis old and falling apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.79,0:11:36.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only a tool could've\Nmade such a clean hole!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.59,0:11:39.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What in the world is it for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.09,0:11:41.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, about this clock...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.01,0:11:46.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right. Let's see...\NIt's a cuckoo-clock...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.51,0:11:47.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.97,0:11:51.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't this it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.81,0:11:53.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes! That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.44,0:11:56.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.40,0:12:00.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like an ordinary\Ncuckoo clock to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.82,0:12:02.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there something to it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.70,0:12:04.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It rings at a certain time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.07,0:12:08.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course it does.\NIt's a cuckoo clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.87,0:12:11.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it happens at a weird time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.12,0:12:14.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every 10:50 or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.42,0:12:19.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And something strange comes\Nout of it instead of a cuckoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.34,0:12:22.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.17,0:12:23.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just watch!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.18,0:12:25.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Should be any time now!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.48,0:12:36.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing's happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.02,0:12:40.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's odd! It came out last time!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.15,0:12:44.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure it isn't just broken?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.11,0:12:45.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course it isn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.70,0:12:48.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our grandfather's clocks\Nare known for never breaking!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.16,0:12:52.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is ridiculous. I'm going home.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.83,0:12:57.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait, Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}! There's another\Nstrange thing that needs solving!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.13,0:12:58.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.00,0:13:03.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The VCR's timer has been set, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.47,0:13:07.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let go! I told you, I'm leaving!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.40,0:13:24.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.20,0:13:30.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's crazy, Dad! All the clocks\Nin the house are ringing!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.08,0:13:33.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-The entire house?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.75,0:13:36.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even the VCR is running!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.75,0:13:40.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What in the world is going on here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.72,0:13:52.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the clocks in the house are ringing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.97,0:13:55.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What in the world is going on here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.61,0:14:02.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It stopped!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.11,0:14:05.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The video ran for only a minute, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.07,0:14:08.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.26,0:14:29.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.63,0:14:31.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.14,0:14:35.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A big cat's taken up lodging in\Nthe attic and we can't get rid of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.47,0:14:38.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, think you can solve\Nthe mystery of the clocks
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.48,0:14:41.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that all ring at the same time\Nevery day at 11:00 a.m.?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.73,0:14:48.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I dunno. Maybe it's just one\Nof your grandfather's pranks?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.36,0:14:50.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But isn't it strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.36,0:14:54.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd use all the clocks in the\Nhouse if I were going to pull a prank,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.99,0:14:57.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it looks like only\Nthe digital clocks rang.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.00,0:14:59.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only the digital clocks?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.54,0:15:00.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.33,0:15:06.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I checked. That cuckoo clock and\Nthis alarm clock were set to "off."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.59,0:15:11.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's right! All the analog\Nclocks are set to "off"!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.55,0:15:14.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure you guys didn't turn them off?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.89,0:15:20.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! We decided not to touch\Nanything until this mystery is solved!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.64,0:15:24.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't just the clocks.\NThis VCR was running, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.61,0:15:25.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,VCR?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.73,0:15:27.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.44,0:15:28.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.86,0:15:34.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Monjiro-{\i1}san {\i0}must've had a TV show\Nhe watched every day at 11:00!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.53,0:15:36.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why he set the alarms!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.24,0:15:39.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But don't you think\Nhe set too many alarms?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.62,0:15:42.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The old guy didn't wake easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.58,0:15:46.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyways, one look at\Nthe video and it'll all be clear!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.92,0:15:48.88,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Play
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.97,0:15:55.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This TV isn't\Nconnected to an antenna!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.68,0:15:57.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would seem not.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.51,0:16:02.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you need to wake up\Nif you had the recorder on a timer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.60,0:16:06.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So why is this video on a timer?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.36,0:16:07.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.40,0:16:10.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look here, at the numbers!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.99,0:16:13.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a weird crack after the zero!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.66,0:16:18.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This digital clock has a crack, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.70,0:16:20.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See! In the same spot!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.16,0:16:23.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so does this one...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.62,0:16:24.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-And this one...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.63,0:16:26.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.71,0:16:32.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that digital clock in the living\Nroom had a similar crack.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.09,0:16:35.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.51,0:16:43.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me this "110" was\Nleft behind by Monjiro-{\i1}san {\i0}as...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.85,0:16:44.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...a code.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.23,0:16:45.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.44,0:16:48.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.86,0:16:55.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If 110 is a code, it'd make sense\Nthat only the digital clocks rang.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.11,0:16:59.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On an analog clock,\N11:00 would just be 11 o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.70,0:17:02.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what could 110 be?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.66,0:17:06.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,110 is the emergency police number...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.87,0:17:09.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And when you think of the police...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.46,0:17:13.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.38,0:17:15.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.14,0:17:18.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dogs!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.80,0:17:21.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The police have police dogs!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.56,0:17:29.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This "110" means we have\Nto find all the dogs in this house!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.11,0:17:35.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Let's split up and\Ngather every dog in the living room!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.99,0:17:40.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One of the dogs has\Nto be hiding something!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.70,0:17:48.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Collie, German Shepherd,\NSiberian Husky, Tosa, Doberman...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.29,0:17:54.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dobermans are police dogs,\Nbut there's nothing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.05,0:17:55.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it's the Dalmatian?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.05,0:17:58.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember the movie about those dogs?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.47,0:18:01.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was "101."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.76,0:18:05.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There might still be some\Nother dogs. Keep looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.73,0:18:07.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.15,0:18:14.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dog, dog, dog...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.99,0:18:19.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The attic...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.16,0:18:29.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's locked!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.22,0:18:47.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now!\NThere's nothing in that room!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.27,0:18:51.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And these stairs are\Ndangerous! There's no handrail!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.52,0:18:54.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now come downstairs with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.90,0:18:57.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-B-But there was someone in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.28,0:18:58.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the cat!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.40,0:19:04.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure the kitty would\Nbe sad if you hurt yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.20,0:19:06.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.49,0:19:10.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}. What do you say\Nwe check the study again?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.96,0:19:11.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,'Kay...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.09,0:19:21.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, those were human eyes!\NWhy is he trying to hide it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.01,0:19:23.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.52,0:19:33.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}. Anything\Nwith a dog design. Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.86,0:19:34.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.98,0:19:37.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's strange. It's too strange!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.61,0:19:42.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's gotta be\Nsomething to this mansion!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.32,0:19:47.33,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,File 'Goblin'
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.70,0:19:46.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"File 'Goblin'"...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.45,0:19:49.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean them?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.91,0:19:59.92,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Bandits of the Wind!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.04,0:19:56.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is! These are articles about\Nthe Goblins, the Bandits of the Wind!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.25,0:19:58.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why are these articles filed here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.38,0:20:05.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Goblins targeted corrupt\Nbusinessmen's safes and illicit deals!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.51,0:20:10.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because they were so swift,\Nthey were called the Bandits of the Wind
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.27,0:20:15.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and they always left creepy\Ngoblin figures wherever they struck.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.56,0:20:21.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The name "Goblin" refers to\Nthe malicious European spirits
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.11,0:20:23.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and familiars that would\Ntake up residence in homes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.91,0:20:27.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They possess a bizarre form.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.66,0:20:36.63,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,They've Stopped!? Mystery of the Goblins
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.62,0:20:36.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been ten years since the\NGoblins ceased their activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.09,0:20:40.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so no one's been caught yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.22,0:20:47.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Estimated to Have Eight\NMembers!! Leader Named 'Demon'"...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.80,0:20:49.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Demon?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.56,0:20:53.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was the name on the golf bag...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.85,0:20:55.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.48,0:20:57.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A mirror?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.07,0:21:03.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? It's attached\Nto the desk! Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.61,0:21:10.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, there was a hole\Nin the wall behind me...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.66,0:21:13.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And right above it\Nis the cuckoo clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.50,0:21:15.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The hole in the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.92,0:21:18.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The immobile mirror\Nfacing the hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.83,0:21:21.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the cuckoo clock opposite\Nit and above the hole...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.35,0:21:33.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.77,0:21:37.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran! I'm coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.81,0:21:41.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Ran?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.73,0:21:43.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-There!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.83,0:21:57.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Demon figures...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.87,0:22:02.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Demons aren't animals! What are\Nsuch creepy things doing there?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.92,0:22:08.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those aren't just demons.\NThey're goblins!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.51,0:22:14.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're definitely what the Bandits\Nof the Wind used to leave behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.56,0:22:17.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why three of them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.35,0:22:23.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just what kind of mystery are\Nthese three goblins hiding?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.48,0:24:05.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Don't tell me those figures are...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.25,0:24:08.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.41,0:24:09.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.27,0:24:12.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.38,0:24:17.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I see what's going on here!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.44,0:24:24.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.34,0:24:27.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next Conan--
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.79,0:24:31.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Case of the Mysterious\NBandit Mansion (Part 2)."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.05,0:24:50.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.52,0:24:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Door.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.70,0:24:53.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode we solve the house's mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.61,0:24:55.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you know it's made of gingerbread?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.64,0:24:56.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.70,0:24:58.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
